NUMBER 257
NAME Elm Street & First
OUTDOOR_OTHER
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Upon this hill a salty air blows from the east. Once lined with beautiful elm trees and clean, pleasant buildings, this intersection now resembles much of the rest of the city with charred stumps and ravaged walls. Work crews scurry diligently to clean the debris, and as the alley to the west is transformed to a new street.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 268
EXIT S 256
EXIT E 258
EXIT W 2801
EXIT ABOVE 2152
ITEM 2 1579 VAL1=294
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
Thick ivy has nearly covered the small building, aided by a row of poorly-trimmed hedges on either side of the door. A small plaque is set into the front of the door.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 4 400 ADJ1=294
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 4
The plaque has a name inscribed upon it over an embossed white rose.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 4
The plaque is inscribed with the name "Corwyn D'Evan" in flowing script, just over an embossed white rose.
*DESCRIPTION_END
