Number 2801
Name First Street Extension, Construction
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
In glaring contrast to some of the worn-torn areas, this renovated and expanding area is booming with activity. You notice more foundations are in place, and more work continues to the west. Various legal postings declaring restoration licenses, commercial licensing, and other affairs have begun to crop up.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 257
EXIT W 2802
;
Number 2802
Name First Street Extension, Construction
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
Construction in earnest has now begun on in this area. Vacant lots are being subdivided now that most of the rubble has been cleared.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 2801
EXIT W 2803
;
Number 2803
Name First Street Extension, Construction
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
This alley is cramped by the overflow of debris from the west. A small amount of excavation seems to be going on, as workers try to broaden the alley to a street width.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 2802
;
NUMBER 2809
NAME O'Berin Way
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
O'Berin's Way leads off from the Bazaar where quaint homes are being constructed to closely hug the narrow cobblestoned street. Passersby stroll along, admiring the craftsmen creating ornate trim and colorful awnings for new windows and doorways. Except for a few flowerboxes, the street is devoid of all shrubbery.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 204
EXIT N 2810
;
NUMBER 2810
NAME O'Berin Way, Construction
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
Taking on the wide open air of the Bazaar further to the south, O'Berin Way now bustles with construction activity. Weaving about you see ancient vacant buildings, long forgotten, being restored. New expansion continues to the north.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 2811
EXIT S 2809
;
NUMBER 2811
NAME O'Berin Way, Construction
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
This rubble-ridden area seems to be a focal point of workers' efforts. You notice some large trenches being dug, perhaps to eventually become foundations.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 2810
;
NUMBER 2812
Name Main Street, West
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
The smell of fresh cut wood permeates this area, as new homes, shops, and other assorted buildings beings in this area. The former alley has now been fully widened to an impressive street width, and a series of solid foundations have been laid. Royal guard outposts have been established along the street perimeter here, but no explanation is offered for their presence.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 250
EXIT W 2813
;
Number 2813
Name Main Street, West
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
This block had been cramped with rubble and work crews, but now seems to be widening. The work crews here seem to move at a brisker pace than others in town. King's sentries now patrol the outer perimeter of the area, in and around the construction sites.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 2812
EXIT W 2814
;
Number 2814
Name Main Street, West
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
This cramped area through the rubble seems to be a focal point of the reconstruction efforts. Some workers are hauling away large sections of old brick and damaged wood supports, while others seem to be digging new foundations.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 2813
